Our IT Staff Augmentation Process

Define Your Requirements

Share your augmentation needs, including tech stack, team size, and staffing period. Detailed requirements help us quickly connect you with ideal candidates.

Select Your Developers

Choose from ready-to-go teams for urgent needs or custom-recruited developers for long-term collaboration. Participate in the selection and interview process if desired.

Onboard Remote Programmers

Integrate augmented staff with your in-house team for smooth collaboration. Brief hires on project details and assign responsibilities to each team member.

Manage Your Extended Team

Your extended team adjusts to your internal schedule and uses the same project management tools. We offer part-time or full-time Project Manager options for team management.

Deliver Your Project

We monitor the project's progress to ensure all requirements are met. The result is a robust digital solution delivered on time and within scope.

FAQs

frequently asked questions

How to Get Hired as a Software Developer?

Develop strong programming skills, create a portfolio of projects, tailor your resume, network in tech circles, apply widely, prepare for interviews, and emphasize soft skills.

How to Recruit Software Engineers?

Craft compelling job descriptions, tap into online platforms like LinkedIn and specialized tech job boards, use employee referrals, and showcase your company’s culture and projects.

How to Find Software Engineers?

Utilize online job boards, social media platforms, coding communities, tech events, and industry-specific networking events to connect with potential software engineers.

Where to Hire Programmers?

Explore freelancing platforms like Upwork, and tech job boards like Stack Overflow Jobs, and consider collaborating with software development agencies to hire skilled programmers.

Where to Hire Software Engineers?

Leverage platforms like LinkedIn, GitHub, Hacker Rank, and industry-specific job boards to find and hire qualified software engineers.

Where to Hire a Software Developer?

Consider job boards like Indeed and Glassdoor, social media platforms, tech-specific communities, and partnering with software development companies to hire proficient software developers.
